<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Hardened-runtime entitlements for the notarized, direct-distribution build.

  The app is intentionally NOT App-Sandboxed (torrenting's listening ports and
  arbitrary user-folder writes fight the sandbox), so network access needs no
  entitlement here. What hardened runtime DOES require:

  * disable-library-validation — the app loads its OWN vendored dylibs
    (libtorrent/OpenSSL/libssh2) from Contents/Frameworks. Without this, those
    loads are rejected under hardened runtime.

  This is accepted by Apple's notary service (it is not an App-Sandbox key).

  allow-jit and allow-unsigned-executable-memory used to be here for the bundled
  yt-dlp, which was PyInstaller-frozen and needed executable memory that was not
  code-signed. That feature is gone, and nothing else in the app JITs, so both
  keys were dropped — the remaining surface is the smaller for it.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
